 'coolie trade' - mainly Asian labourers transferred to French and British islands in the Indian Ocean, Australia, Indonesia, South Africa, the Caribbean, the Americas, as well as to Portuguese colonies in Africa - was one of the largest migration movements in global history. Indentured contract workers are perhaps the most revealing example of bonded labour in the grey area between the poles of chattel slavery and 'free' wage labour.This interdisciplinary volume addresses historically and regionally specific cases of bonded labour relations from the 18th century to sponsorship systems in the Arab Gulf States today.  afunded by Knowledge Unlatched - KU Select 2018: Backlist Collection  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aForced laborxHistoryvCongresses. 0aIndentured servantsxHistoryvCongresses. 0aLabor contractxHistoryvCongresses. 0aLabor policyxHistoryvCongresses. 0aPeonagexHistoryvCongresses. 0aSlave laborxHistoryvCongresses. 4aColonialism. 4aCulture. 4aEthnology. 4aGlobal History. 4aGlobalization. 4aHistory of Colonialism. 4aHistory. 4aMigration. 4aPostcolonialism. 4aSocial History. 4aWork. 7aHISTORY / World.2bisacsh  aColonialism.  aCulture.  aEthnology.  aGlobal History.  aGlobalization.  aHistory of Colonialism.  aHistory.  aMigration.  aPostcolonialism.  aSocial History.  aWork.1 aAbel, Johanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDamir-Geilsdorf, Sabine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDamir-Geilsdorf, Sabine, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGómez-Popescu, Liliana, e